The process hazard analysis was performed by a team with expertise in engineering and process operations.  Don Love, Ph.D, P.E. facilitated the effort.  Dr. Love has over 50 years of experience and knowledge specific to the process being evaluated.  
SPC has established a system to promptly address the team's findings and recommendations.  SPC also assures that recommendations are resolved in a timely manner and resolutions are documented.  SPC developed a written schedule of when these actions are to be completed.  SPC has communicated the actions to operating, maintenance and other employees whose work assignments are in the process and who may be affected by the recommendations or actions.
The process hazard analysis will be updated and revalidated every 5 years, in accordance with CFR 1910.119(e), to assure consistency with the current process.  All MOC (Management of Change) items will be reviewed at the time of re-evaluation to ensure all process changes are evaluated for hazards and hazard controls.  The updates or revalidations for each process, and the documented resolution of recommendations, will be kept for the life of the process.
